<h1>CommerceIQ AI</h1>
<h2>Database Design Document (DDD)</h2>
<hr />
<h2>1. Database Overview</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Database Engine</strong>: PostgreSQL 16+</li>
<li><strong>Architecture</strong>: Multi-Tenant SaaS Architecture</li>
<li><strong>Scale</strong>: 100k+ Products, 50k+ Customers, 10k+ Vendors, 1M+ Orders, 10k+ Daily Trans.</li>
<li><strong>Target Audience</strong>: Database Architects, Backend Developers, DevOps, QA.</li>
</ul>
<h2>2. Database Architecture</h2>
<p>CommerceIQ AI utilizes a highly normalized (3NF) relational database architecture. Multi-tenancy is logically separated via the <code>vendor_id</code> and <code>tenant_id</code> columns, ensuring data isolation.</p>
<h2>3. Database Standards &amp; Naming Conventions</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Tables</strong>: Plural <code>snake_case</code> (e.g., <code>product_categories</code>).</li>
<li><strong>Columns</strong>: Singular <code>snake_case</code> (e.g., <code>user_id</code>, <code>created_at</code>).</li>
<li><strong>Primary Keys</strong>: <code>id</code> of type <code>UUID</code>.</li>
<li><strong>Foreign Keys</strong>: <code>[entity]_id</code> (e.g., <code>vendor_id</code>).</li>
<li><strong>Indexes</strong>: <code>idx_[table]_[column]</code> (e.g., <code>idx_users_email</code>).</li>
</ul>
<h2>4. Common Table Standards</h2>
<p>Every table includes standard audit columns:
*   <code>id</code> (UUID, Primary Key)
*   <code>created_at</code> (TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE, NOT NULL, DEFAULT NOW())
*   <code>updated_at</code> (TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE, NOT NULL, DEFAULT NOW())
*   <code>created_by</code> (UUID, NULLABLE)
*   <code>updated_by</code> (UUID, NULLABLE)
*   <code>is_active</code> (BOOLEAN, NOT NULL, DEFAULT TRUE)
*   <code>is_deleted</code> (BOOLEAN, NOT NULL, DEFAULT FALSE)</p>
<hr />
